The '''ChÃ¢teau de Cerisy-la-Salle''', located in the French commune of [[Cerisy-la-Salle]] (in the [[Manche]] ''[[dÃ©partement]]'', region of [[Normandy]]), hosts the '''Centre culturel international de Cerisy-la-Salle (CCIC)''', a prestigious venue for intellectual and scholarly encounters founded in 1952 by [[Anne Heurgon-Desjardins]]. The center is the home of the famous '''''"Colloques de Cerisy"''''' ("Cerisy Conferences"), a series of seminars which constitute an important reference in the recent history of French intellectual life. The expression ''"Colloque de Cerisy"'' also refers to the proceedings of these seminars, available from various publishers.

