'''Doctor of Theology''' ({{lang-la|Doctor Theologiae}}, abbreviated '''DTh''', '''ThD''', '''DTheol''', or '''Dr. theol.''') is a [[terminal degree]] in the academic discipline of [[theology]]. The ThD is an advanced research degree equivalent to the [[Doctor of Philosophy]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Structure of U.S. Education Systems: Research Doctorate Degrees|url=https://www2.ed.gov/about/offices/list/ous/international/usnei/us/doctorate.doc|publisher=U.S. Department of Education|accessdate=18 January 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Degree Program Standards|url=https://www.ats.edu/uploads/accrediting/documents/degree-program-standards.pdf|website=ATS|publisher=Association of Theological Schools|accessdate=18 January 2018}}</ref>
== Terminology == In the academic study of theology, which is deeply rooted in the Christian tradition, doctoral students are often conferred a Doctor of Theology, a [[Doctor of Philosophy]], a [[Doctor of Ministry]], a [[Doctor of Practical Theology]] or Doctor of Sacred Theology. However, the [[Doctor of Ministry]] is generally understood as a [[professional doctorate]]. === United States === In the United States, some of the older theological seminaries began offering the Doctor of Theology as an equivalent to the research [[Doctor of Philosophy]]. In [[Princeton Theological Seminary]], for example, this practice was inherited from the German system of education since the professors involved in establishing the doctoral program were trained in German Universities. Princeton Theological Seminary has since switched to using Doctor of Philosophy as its main designation.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://phd75.ptsem.edu/history/|title=History - PhD Anniversary|last=|first=|date=|website=phd75.ptsem.edu|publisher=Princeton Theological Seminary|access-date=23 August 2016}}</ref> A similar shift happened at [[Harvard Divinity School]] in 2015.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://hds.harvard.edu/academics/degree-programs|title=Degree Programs|last=|first=|date=|website=hds.harvard.edu|publisher=Harvard Divinity School|access-date=23 August 2016}}</ref> The only [[Association of Theological Schools]] accredited schools currently accepting students to ThD programs are:<ref>{{cite web|title=Member School Advanced Search|url=https://www.ats.edu/member-schools/member-school-advanced-search?title=&field_ms_primary_denomination_value=&field_ms_degrees_offered_value=ThD&field_ms_has_comprehensive_value=&circle_op=%3C&circle[value]=&circle[unit]=miles&circle[location]=|website=ATS|publisher=Association of Theological Schools|accessdate=13 March 2018}}</ref>
*[[Duke Divinity School]] *[[Graduate Theological Union]] *[[Interdenominational Theological Center]] *[[Seventh-day Adventist Theological Seminary]] *[[Evangel Theological Seminary]] *[[Columbia Theological Seminary]] *[[General Theological Seminary]] *[[Evangelical Seminary]]
=== United Kingdom === In the United Kingdom, the Doctor of Theology is a fairly new doctoral program. Certain universities have begun offering it as a form of practical doctorate, comparable to the [[Doctor of Ministry]] in the United States.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.winchester.ac.uk/Studyhere/Pages/professional-doctorate-in-theology-and-practice.aspx|title=Professional Doctorate in Theology and Practice|last=|first=|date=|website=www.winchester.ac.uk|publisher=University of Winchester|access-date=23 August 2016}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.roehampton.ac.uk/postgraduate-courses/Practical-Theology-DTh/|title=Practical Theology DTh|last=|first=|date=|website=www.roehampton.ac.uk|publisher=University of Roehampton|access-date=23 August 2016}}</ref> To offer a doctorate that helping distinguishes the more practical nature of the degree, some British universities have adopted the term [[Doctor of Practical Theology]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.birmingham.ac.uk/postgraduate/courses/research/thr/practical-theology-doctorate.aspx|title=DPT Practical Theology Doctorate|last=|first=|date=|website=www.birmingham.ac.uk|publisher=University of Birmingham|access-date=23 August 2016}}</ref>
